>>__ Parse.temp_set_grammars $ valOf $ grammarDB {thyname="hol"};
## `CURRY_CONV`

``` hol4
PairRules.CURRY_CONV : conv
```

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Currys an application of a paired abstraction.

### Example

``` hol4
>>__ load "PairRules";

>> PairRules.CURRY_CONV (Term `(\(x,y). x + y) (1,2)`);

>> PairRules.CURRY_CONV (Term `(\(x,y). x + y) z`);
```

### Failure

`CURRY_CONV tm` fails if `tm` is not an application of a paired
abstraction.

### See also

[`PairRules.UNCURRY_CONV`](#PairRules.UNCURRY_CONV)
